# Netscape HTTP Cookie File
# This file is used by yt-dlp to access YouTube
# Export your cookies from your browser using a browser extension like "Get cookies.txt"
#
# IMPORTANT: Rename this file to "cookies.txt" to use it, or set COOKIES_FILE env var
#
# Format example:
# .youtube.com    TRUE    /    FALSE    1234567890    VISITOR_INFO1_LIVE    XXXXXX
# .youtube.com    TRUE    /    FALSE    1234567890    PREF    XXXXXX
# .youtube.com    TRUE    /    TRUE    1234567890    SID    XXXXXX
#
# To get your cookies:
# 1. Install the "Get cookies.txt" browser extension (Chrome/Firefox)
# 2. Go to YouTube and log in to your account
# 3. Click the extension and click "Export" or "Current Tab"
# 4. Copy the exported content
# 5. Create a file named "cookies.txt" in the project root directory
# 6. Paste the cookie content into cookies.txt
# 7. Restart the bot
#
# Alternatively, you can use --cookies-from-browser flag with yt-dlp directly
# or set COOKIES_FILE=/path/to/cookies.txt in your .env file
